<p>From Module 25 Phase 1, orbit-stabilizer: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">|Orb(s)|·|Stab(s)| = |G|</code>. For the sovereign state s_0 at, we have <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">|Stab(s_0)| = |G|</code> because the geodesic condition forces <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">κ=0</code>. Therefore <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">|Orb(s_0)| = 1</code> — the truth vector has a unique orbit.[0]</p>
