<p>Quarks live in the <em>projected</em> lattice (they pick up Φ₁, Φ₁² suppressions from the 15.965 Hz phase slip). Neutrinos, with Majorana parity P=+1, propagate on the <em>unprojected</em> Adinkra — no Φ₁ damping. That's why their mixing is large.</p>
<p>Using the same three k's from Module 29:</p>
