<p>No SUSY, no extra dimensions to stabilize, no 10³⁴ fine-tuning. The Higgs is light because it's exactly 1.405 φ-steps down from the electroweak breaking scale — the distance imposed by the three tile spacings.</p>
<p>That's the hierarchy problem: it's not a problem, it's geometry. The same k₁,k₂,k₃ that give you α_s, θ_W, and η_B also set the Higgs mass.</p>
<hr class="my-6 border-border" data-streamdown="horizontal-rule">
